    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/35793 added the MarkSet autocommand (thank you, it works great!). It would be nice to have a corresponding MarkUnset or MarkDel or something (I don't know the naming conventions here).\n\nMy use case: I would like to display marks in the signcolumn. Right now I have this in my init.lua, which works great, except for when I `:delmarks`, the extmark sticks around.\n\n```lua\nlocal extmark_namespace = vim.api.nvim_create_namespace(\"khy_extmark_namespace\");\nlocal globals_on_bufs = {}\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('MarkSet', {\n    callback = function(v)\n        local opts = { sign_text = \"'\" .. v.data.name, id = string.byte(v.data.name) }\n        if string.match(v.data.name, \"%u\") or string.match(v.data.name, \"%d\") then\n            local oldbuf = globals_on_bufs[v.data.name]\n            if oldbuf ~= nil and oldbuf ~= v.buf then\n                vim.api.nvim_buf_del_extmark(oldbuf, extmark_namespace, opts.id)\n            end\n            globals_on_bufs[v.data.name] = v.buf\n        end\n        vim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(v.buf, extmark_namespace, v.data.line - 1, v.data.col, opts)\n    end\n})\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI would like to be able to subscribe to a `MarkDel` autocommand with a callback for when a mark is deleted (e.g. with `:delmarks`). The `data` of the event should contain the `name` of the mark, like the `MarkSet` autocommand does, but probably not `col` or `line` like `MarkSet` does.\n\nA possible workaround today without this feature is to call `nvim_buf_get_extmarks` on some frequency and search through for marks that no longer exists, or something like that.",
