            "body": "> see [#37284 (comment)](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/37284#issuecomment-4119376066)\n\nfrom that comment\n\n> I think that either an additional flag, or just documenting that `line == col == 0` means delete would work perfectly, when also triggering `MarkSet` in `ex_delmarks`.\n\nyes, that would also work nicely! no need to create a new autocommand if it's documented that `line == col == 0` means delete (and it actually works that way).\n\n> it appears there is a workaround already\n\nI don't think that's the case - `MarkSet` is not triggered in `ex_delmarks`. So I suppose, this issue could also be viewed as a feature request to trigger `MarkSet` in `:delmarks`.\n\n(I don't particularly care *how* I get a notification that a mark has been `:delm`'d, just that there is _some_ way for me to know)",
